{
  "texts": [
    "Experimental tests indicated that a mix containing 2.5% eggshell powder and 5% POFA, resulting in a total of 7.5% cement substitution, produced optimal results.",
    "This combination was found to improve the strength of SCC after 28 days of curing.",
    "However, it was also observed that exceeding a 7.5% replacement ratio could adversely affect the concrete strength.",
    "Glass, one of the oldest man-made materials, has been utilized for over 9,000 years, primarily due to its wide availability and useful properties.",
    "It currently makes up about 4.6% of the 11.6 million metric tons of municipal solid waste (MSW) produced annually."
  ]
}